 the rationale underpinning them.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEthnomethodology. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aCicourel.  aConversation analysis.  aEthnomethodology.  aGarfinkel.  aGoffman.  aPhenomenology.  aResearch methodology.  aSchutz.  aSimmel.  aSociological theory.1 aHammersley, Martyn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2018 eBook-Packagez978311128277040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152612463040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526124630423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526124630/original  a978-3-11-128277-0  Manchester University Press 2018 eBook-Packageb2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles